{"name": "irctk-bot", "metadata": {"name": "irctk-bot", "version": "0.1.0", "classifiers": ["License :: Other/Proprietary License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12"], "home_page": null, "license": "BSD", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["irc-toolkit"], "summary": "Bot framework for irctk", "upload_time": 1732916740}, "documentation": ["# irctk-bot\n\nBot framework for irctk. irctk-bot can be installed from PyPI.\n\nUsage:\n\n```shell\n$ irctk-bot -h irc.example.com -m irctk_bot.modules.ping\n```\n\nWhere module is the Python module name to any modules you wish to load, you may\nprovide `-m` multiple times.\n\nAlternatively, you may use a config file, see `example.toml`.\n\n```\n$ irctk-bot -c example.toml\n```\n\n## Writing a module\n\nExpose an instance of the `Module` class as a global `module` property to a\nPython module. Use the `Module.command` decorator to register commands.\n\n```python\nfrom irctk_bot import Context, Module\n\nmodule = Module()\n\ndef ping(context: Context, name: Optional[str] = None) -> None:\n    if name:\n        return context.reply(f'pong {name}')\n    context.reply('pong')\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "irctk_bot.modules", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "irctk_bot.modules.ping", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "irctk_bot.modules.ping.ping", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "context", "type": {"name": "Context", "xref": {"fqname": "irctk_bot.context.Context", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "irctk_bot.modules.ping.module", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "irctk_bot.modules.help", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "irctk_bot.modu